{
  "texts": [
    "Running effects within the LEFT are particularly significant for the dipole operators L dγ and L dG entering B → X s γ, as well as for the scalar and tensor operators L S,RL νedu, L S,RR νedu and L T,RR νedu, which enter observables in the charged-current b → c(u)ℓν transitions.",
    "We consistently use tree-level SMEFT-to-LEFT matching conditions, except for operators contributing to B → X s γ where, given the relevance of the constraint and the size of loop corrections, we implement one-loop matching conditions following [48] (see section 3.3 for more details).Once all observables have been expressed in terms of SMEFT WCs at the scale Λ NP, we impose the U(2) 5 symmetry.",
    "3 All theory expressions now depend on the 124 WCs of the U(2) 5 -symmetric SMEFT, which we collectively denote as ⃗ C(Λ NP).",
    "At this stage, we construct the likelihood for each sector S = {EW, flavor, collider} asχ 2 S ( ⃗ C(Λ NP)) = ij∈S O th i ( ⃗ C(Λ NP)) -O exp i σ -2 ij O th j ( ⃗ C(Λ NP)) -O exp j, (3.6)whereO th i ( ⃗ C(Λ NP))is the theory prediction for the observable O i written in terms of the high-scale U(2) 5 -symmetric Wilson coefficients, O exp i is the corresponding experimental value and σ ij is the covariance matrix for O i and O j.",
    "The global likelihood is then given by the sum of the individual likelihoods:χ 2 tot = χ 2 EW + χ 2 flavor + χ 2 collider."
  ]
}